      • getBackdatedSessions

        public java.lang.Object[][] getBackdatedSessions(java.lang.String symbol,
                                        int expiryMonths,
                                        int lastDay,
                                        long backdatedTime)
                                          throws java.sql.SQLException,
                                                 java.lang.ClassNotFoundException
        Returns an array of information about backdated sessions for backtesting.
        Parameters:
        symbol - the contract symbol e.g.: "HSI", "NQ"
        expiryMonths - number of months that a contract expiry
        lastDay - number of days before expiry to roll over
        backdatedTime - backdated time in milliseconds
        Returns:
        an array with columns: "m_localSymbol", "timeZone", "day_open", "day_close", "break_start", "break_end"
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException
        java.lang.ClassNotFoundException
